127
00:12:49,857 --> 00:12:53,527
No. No, you can't do this to us.

128
00:12:53,611 --> 00:12:56,906
They were waiting for your husband
to turn himself in, and he never did.

129
00:13:02,953 --> 00:13:04,955
Ma'am? Ma'am.

130
00:13:05,664 --> 00:13:07,750
May I give you some advice?

131
00:13:11,503 --> 00:13:15,341
I think it's time for you to think
about you and your children's safety.

132
00:13:15,424 --> 00:13:16,967
Forget about him.

133
00:13:38,364 --> 00:13:41,826
 The kids miss you.
Should I wake up Juan Pablo?

134
00:13:43,702 --> 00:13:47,164
Probably not a good idea
right now, my love.

135
00:13:48,499 --> 00:13:51,419
So... do you feel a year older or what?

136
00:13:53,420 --> 00:13:55,714
More like four or five.

137
00:13:56,382 --> 00:13:58,384
We've missed you very much, Pablo.

138
00:13:59,009 --> 00:14:00,761
The days feel longer.

139
00:14:03,681 --> 00:14:05,224
For me too.

140
00:14:07,434 --> 00:14:09,770
I still don't understand
why you're in Medellín.

141
00:14:09,853 --> 00:14:12,022
That place is too dangerous, my love.

142
00:14:15,901 --> 00:14:19,571
