No one would think I'd be here.

143
00:14:22,032 --> 00:14:22,908
Pablo...

144
00:14:23,992 --> 00:14:27,704
I think the time has come.
We don't have a choice.

145
00:14:29,665 --> 00:14:32,710
Turning yourself in
isn't the end of the world, my love.

146
00:14:32,793 --> 00:14:34,086
You can survive prison.

147
00:14:37,297 --> 00:14:40,300
We both know that won't happen.

148
00:14:40,384 --> 00:14:42,678
Stop, stop, stop, stop! Shh!

149
00:14:43,429 --> 00:14:45,848
-  Listen to me, Pablo.
- They're talking.

150
00:14:45,931 --> 00:14:48,851
- You will always be Pablo Escobar.
- Boss.

151
00:14:48,934 --> 00:14:52,187
You will always be that man
that's admired and followed.

152
00:14:52,271 --> 00:14:53,814
My man.

153
00:14:54,690 --> 00:14:57,318
My love, there's a lot of journalists
who want to speak with you.

154
00:14:57,401 --> 00:14:59,236
The people love you and follow you.

155
00:14:59,903 --> 00:15:02,280
Tata, Limón wants me off.

156
00:15:02,364 --> 00:15:05,534
It's Escobar. Let's go west!
Fix the position, Morales.

157
00:15:07,286 --> 00:15:09,622
My love, look at Nelson Mandela.

158
00:15:11,248 --> 00:15:14,334
They put the man in jail,
but the people still believed in him.

159
00:15:14,418 --> 00:15:16,337
They gave him the Nobel Prize.

160
00:15:16,420 --> 00:15:21,342
They say he may even become president.
President, Pablo.

161
00:15:21,425 --> 00:15:23,343
Of the same country that imprisoned him.

162
00:15:23,427 --> 00:15:25,429
 I need to hang up.
We'll talk about this later.

163
00:15:25,512 --> 00:15:27,181
Alvaro, stop. Stop for a second.

164
00:15:27,264 --> 00:15:30,058
 All right, Pablo.
But think about what I'm saying.

165
00:15:30,142 --> 00:15:32,019
It's very important.

166
00:15:32,102 --> 00:15:35,147
It's our only way out really.

167
00:15:35,898 --> 00:15:37,817
Alvaro, let's go slowly.

168
00:15:38,484 --> 00:15:40,695
Colonel!
Colonel, this is Lieutenant Martinez.

169
00:15:40,778 --> 00:15:43,698
Think about turning yourself in, my love.
Think of your family.

170
00:15:43,781 --> 00:15:45,157
I'll think about it.

171
00:15:46,074 --> 00:15:47,367
All right?

172
00:15:50,162 --> 00:15:51,830
I love you very much.

173
00:16:24,071 --> 00:16:25,322
Where are you going?

174
00:16:25,906 --> 00:16:27,199
To Medellín.

175
00:16:27,282 --> 00:16:31,828
